THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 391A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Department shall develop or otherwise prescribe for
4 administration pursuant to subsection 3:
5 (a) A school climate survey to gather data from school staff for
6 the purpose of evaluating the school climate in the public schools
7 in this State.
8 (b) An exit and transfer survey to gather data from teachers
9 who transfer, resign or are dismissed for the purpose of improving
10 the efforts of this State to attract and retain teachers.
11 2. The Department may partner with any person or entity
12 with expertise in education or data collection and survey
13 administration to assist with developing a survey pursuant to this
14 section.
15 3. The board of trustees of a school district shall administer:
16 (a) The school climate survey developed or prescribed
17 pursuant to paragraph (a) of subsection 1 to each member of the
18 staff of each school within the school district once each school
19 year.
20 (b) The exit and transfer survey developed or prescribed
21 pursuant to paragraph (b) of subsection 1 to each teacher upon
22 the transfer, resignation or dismissal of the teacher from a school
23 in the school district.
24 4. The board of trustees of a school district may partner with
25 the Department and any other person or entity with expertise in
26 data collection and survey administration to assist with
27 administering and collecting the responses of a survey pursuant to
28 this section.
29 5. On or before December 1 of each year, the board of
30 trustees of a school district shall report to the Department a
31 summary of the information that the board of trustees has received
32 from administering the surveys pursuant to subsection 3 in the
33 immediately preceding 12 months. The board of trustees must also
34 include with the report the raw data collected in connection with
35 the surveys if the Department requests such data.
36 6. On or before February 1 of each year, the Department
37 shall develop and publish on an Internet website maintained by
38 the Department a written report containing a summary of the
