1 information received from each school district pursuant to
2 subsection 5 within the immediately preceding year.
3 7. As used in this section, “school climate” means the basis of
4 which to measure the relationships between pupils and the parents
5 or legal guardians of pupils and educational personnel, the
6 cultural and linguistic competence of instructional materials and
7 educational personnel, the emotional and physical safety of pupils
8 and educational personnel and the social, emotional and academic
9 development of pupils and educational personnel.
10 Sec. 2. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
11 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
12 provisions of this act.
13 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
